// PKL-128c: Apple Pkl's multi-argument constraint form
// (`Int(isPositive, isLessThan(10))`) composes predicates by
// listing them comma-separated. Each predicate must hold for the
// value to be accepted; the constraint dispatcher trims whitespace
// around each split so spacing inside the parens stays cosmetic.
small: Int(isPositive, isLessThan(10)) = 5

bigger: Int(isPositive, isLessThan(100)) = 42

negative: Int(!isPositive) = -3
